top.value: The objective of the financing is to help develop 50MWac contracted solar power generation capacity.

The objective of the project is to contribute to reducing the high rice import and enhance economic growth through improved production, processing, and marketing, and enhancing private sector participation
The objective of the project is to provide a Line of Finance to the Turk EXIM Bank  to finance infrastructure and industrial projects in IDB member countries.

The objective of the project is to contribute towards satisfying the increasing demand for electricity in the region by supplying an additional 1,348 GWh per annum (946 GWh from Kaleta HEPP (in Guinea) and 402 GWh from Sambangalou Hydro Electric Power Plant or about 12% of their electrical energy needs in 2020.

The objective of the project is to develop balanced fertilizer and integrated soil fertility management recommendations targeted to specific crops, under specific soil and agro-climatic conditions that will sustainably increase yields and nutritional quality and result in increased returns on fertilizer investments.

The objective of the project is to expand access to affordable and improved housing, equipped with associated basic infrastructure as well as social and market facilities, for the rural population in six (6) regions of Uzbekistan.

The objective of the project is to contribute to the socio-economic development of Senegal through financial inclusion of small and micro entrepreneurs, leading to greater jobs, greater economic activity, and improved livelihoods through focusing on the agricultural and services value chains that will broaden employment and income opportunities.

The objective of the project is to contribute to the enhancement of livestock production for increased revenues and reduced food insecurity in the Sahel region through improved natural resources management, access to markets, and increased control of transboundary livestock diseases.
The objective of the project is to contribute to the improvement of health and wellbeing of Pakistani children through eradication of Polio.

The main objective of the project is to contribute to increasing the incomes of actors along the rice value chain and ensure food and nutritional security. It will also contribute to (i) increasing the production of rice, market garden products and fishing products; (ii) improving the transformation and marketing capacities of actors; and (iii) supporting the organization of actors in the project area. More specifically, this project ambitions to develop transformative initiatives that will increase the production and productivity of agriculture (rice, Vegetables etc.), and fishery value chains towards significantly improving the lives and livelihoods of farmer communities in Sassandra and Fromager Regions.
